 * This is a convenient way of defining what classes of cars can race on what
 * tracks. Each top-level object contains
 *  - a list of tracks (name -> [configurations])
 *  - a list of representative cars
 *
 * representativeClasses are resolved to all the classes at the same level in
 * the same discipline.
 *
 * Each top-level object represents a source of (ideally, real-world) data that
 * says these cars can race on this track.
 */
